***  How to install android sdk in mac **********

	note: you must have to have installed java, eclipse, xcode as well
	
	1. open terminal:

	2.install homebrew :
	ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
	(brew doctor will help to make sure homebrewer is installed or not)

	3. Brew install android-sdk
	(if different path then:
	export ANDROID_HOME=/usr/local/Cellar/android-sdk/24.3.3)
	
	4. setup environment variable or setup bash profile:
	sudo nano ~/.bash_profile
	export $ANDROID_HOME=/Users/shahidulislam/Library/Android/sdk
	export PATH=$PATH:$ANDROID_HOME/tools:$ANDROID_HOME/platform-tools

	5. Android ADT plugin in eclipse: 
	click help ---> new install software ---> paste below link (https://dl-ssl.google.com/android/eclipse/)----> click next and so on.

==========Dafault sdk home path for MAC================:

		/Users/shahidulislam/Library/Android/sdk

=========To open UIAutomatorviewer in MAC==============


	1. Open terminal: 
	2. Go to tools file label using below command:
	 cd Library/Android/sdk/tools
	3. Type uiautomatoeviewer
	4. Hit Enter










